docs.abstract: Salvaged items have been the focus of a tussle over who gets to own a part of the ocean liner’s history. The likely buyers, three hedge funds, are willing to pay $19.5 million.
docs.snippet: Salvaged items have been the focus of a tussle over who gets to own a part of the ocean liner’s history. The likely buyers, three hedge funds, are willing to pay $19.5 million.
docs.lead_paragraph: Some of the richest people in the world lost everything when the Titanic sank. Now a consortium of new-money risk takers is poised to profit from turn-of-the-20th-century artifacts that curators had hoped to claim.

headline.main: The Titanic’s Artifacts Are About to Change Hands. Here’s What’s for Sale.
headline.print_headline: Fate of Titanic Trove? New Owners Say Only That It Will Be Shown

docs.abstract: Primera Air’s efforts to expand couldn’t overcome a competitive market and rising fuel costs. Its abrupt end meant canceled flights in North America and Europe.
docs.snippet: Primera Air’s efforts to expand couldn’t overcome a competitive market and rising fuel costs. Its abrupt end meant canceled flights in North America and Europe.
docs.lead_paragraph: Primera Air, a small low-cost airline that spent the last year expanding its reach from northern Europe to hubs in North America, filed for bankruptcy and ceased flying on Monday night, leaving passengers stranded at airports on both sides of the Atlantic.

headline.main: Passengers Are Stranded as Another European Airline Collapses

docs.abstract: The German carmaker’s United States unit, the only division still turning out the curvy car originally developed at Hitler’s direction, will end production of the vehicle in July.
docs.snippet: The German carmaker’s United States unit, the only division still turning out the curvy car originally developed at Hitler’s direction, will end production of the vehicle in July.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Volkswagen Beetle — the curvy car developed at Adolf Hitler’s direction that became an improbable symbol of the hippie counterculture of the 1960s — is set to become a thing of the past.

headline.main: Volkswagen Beetle, Symbol of ’60s Counterculture, Will Be Discontinued Again
headline.print_headline: Beetle, a Symbol of ’60s Counterculture, Will Be Discontinued Again

byline.original: By Amie Tsang and Jack Ewing

docs.abstract: The quarantine of a flight to New York was followed by sick passengers reported on flights into Philadelphia. But experts say events like this are rare.
docs.snippet: The quarantine of a flight to New York was followed by sick passengers reported on flights into Philadelphia. But experts say events like this are rare.
docs.lead_paragraph: A pair of flights from Europe landed at Philadelphia International Airport on Thursday and their passengers were sent for medical reviews. A day earlier, a plane from Dubai, United Arab Emirates, was quarantined briefly at Kennedy International Airport in New York after initial reports of as many as 100 sick travelers on board.

headline.main: Quarantined Aircraft and Sick Passengers. It’s Not as Scary as It Sounds.
headline.print_headline: A Bevy of Sick Passengers, Quarantines and Questions

docs.abstract: The Bank of England isn’t taking nominations yet, but that hasn’t stopped people from offering names and placing bets.
docs.snippet: The Bank of England isn’t taking nominations yet, but that hasn’t stopped people from offering names and placing bets.
docs.lead_paragraph: The 50-pound bill, worth about $65, is rarely used in everyday life in Britain, but that hasn’t stopped Britons from trying to get their favorites to be the face of a forthcoming design of the note.

headline.main: Who Will Be the Face of the £50 Bill? Probably Not a Soccer Player Riding a Unicorn
headline.print_headline: Who Will Be the Face of the Redesigned £50 Bill?

docs.abstract: From his management style to his personal life, the Tesla chief seems comfortable with chaos, often of his own creation. Is that best for his company?
docs.snippet: From his management style to his personal life, the Tesla chief seems comfortable with chaos, often of his own creation. Is that best for his company?
docs.lead_paragraph: Elon Musk was up early on Saturday. He departed Los Angeles, where he runs SpaceX, his private rocket venture, and flew north in his white Gulfstream jet. Stopping in Silicon Valley, he picked up two engineers from Tesla, his electric-car company. They flew on to Reno, Nev., where they spent the day at Tesla’s battery plant, the Gigafactory.

headline.main: In Elon Musk’s World, Brakes Are for Cars, Not C.E.O.s
headline.print_headline: In Elon Musk’s World,  Brakes Are for Cars, Not C.E.O.s
